To create this, I will use **Marked.js** for high-speed markdown parsing and **Highlight.js** to make the code blocks look professional. I've styled it with a modern "Developer Dark Mode" aesthetic using a clean, split-pane layout.

You can save the code below as an `.html` file (e.g., `previewer.html`) and open it in any browser.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Pro Markdown Previewer</title>
    
    <!-- Libraries -->
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/marked/9.1.2/marked.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/11.8.0/highlight.min.js"></script>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/highlight.js/11.8.0/styles/github-dark.min.css">
    
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg-color: #0d1117;
            --panel-bg: #161b22;
            --text-color: #c9d1d9;
            --accent-color: #58a6ff;
            --border-color: #30363d;
            --header-bg: #010409;
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        body {
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: var(--text-color);
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        /* Header Styling */
        header {
            background-color: var(--header-bg);
            padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: center;
        }

        header h1 {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: var(--accent-color);
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .badge {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            background: var(--border-color);
            padding: 2px 8px;
            border-radius: 12px;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        /* Main Layout */
        main {
            display: flex;
            flex: 1;
            overflow: hidden; /* Prevents body scroll, allows panel scroll */
        }

        .panel {
            flex: 1;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            height: 100%;
        }

        .panel-header {
            background: var(--panel-bg);
            padding: 5px 15px;
            font-size: 0.7rem;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
            color: #8b949e;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        /* Editor Styling */
        #editor {
            flex: 1;
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            color: #e6edf3;
            padding: 20px;
            font-family: 'Fira Code', 'Cascadia Code', 'Source Code Pro', monospace;
            font-size: 14px;
            line-height: 1.6;
            border: none;
            resize: none;
            outline: none;
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border-color);
        }

        /* Preview Styling */
        #preview {
            flex: 1;
            padding: 30px;
            overflow-y: auto;
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        /* Markdown Content Styling (GitHub-ish) */
        #preview h1, #preview h2, #preview h3 { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-bottom: 0.3em; margin-top: 1.5em; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        #preview h1 { font-size: 2em; }
        #preview h2 { font-size: 1.5em; }
        #preview p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        #preview code { background: rgba(110, 118, 129, 0.4); padding: 0.2em 0.4em; border-radius: 6px; font-family: monospace; }
        #preview pre { background: #161b22; padding: 16px; border-radius: 8px; overflow: auto; margin-bottom: 1rem; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
        #preview pre code { background: none; padding: 0; }
        #preview blockquote { padding: 0 1em; color: #8b949e; border-left: 0.25em solid var(--border-color); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        #preview ul, #preview ol { padding-left: 2em; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        #preview a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; }
        #preview a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
        #preview table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
        #preview th, #preview td { border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 6px 13px; }
        #preview tr:nth-child(2n) { background-color: var(--panel-bg); }

        /* Responsive */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            main { flex-direction: column; }
            #editor { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
    <h1>Markdown<span>Live</span></h1>
    <div class="badge">Editor + Preview</div>
</header>

<main>
    <!-- Left Side: Editor -->
    <section class="panel">
        <div class="panel-header">Markdown Input</div>
        <textarea id="editor" spellcheck="false" placeholder="Type your markdown here..."></textarea>
    </section>

    <!-- Right Side: Preview -->
    <section class="panel">
        <div class="panel-header">Live Render</div>
        <div id="preview"></div>
    </section>
</main>

<script>
    const editor = document.getElementById('editor');
    const preview = document.getElementById('preview');

    // Default Content
    const defaultContent = `# Welcome to the Previewer!

## Features:
1. **Live Rendering** - See changes instantly.
2. **Syntax Highlighting** for code blocks.
3. *Italic* and **Bold** text support.
4. [Clickable Links](https://google.com)

### Code Example
\`\`\`javascript
function helloWorld() {
  console.log("Hello, markdown!");
}
helloWorld();
\`\`\`

### List Support
- Item One
- Item Two
  - Sub item A
  - Sub item B

> "Markdown is intended to be as easy-to-read and easy-to-write as is feasible." - John Gruber`;

    // Configure Marked with Highlight.js
    marked.setOptions({
        highlight: function(code, lang) {
            const language = hljs.getLanguage(lang) ? lang : 'plaintext';
            return hljs.highlight(code, { language }).value;
        },
        langPrefix: 'hljs language-', 
        breaks: true,
        gfm: true
    });

    // Update Function
    function updatePreview() {
        const content = editor.value;
        preview.innerHTML = marked.parse(content);
    }

    // Event Listeners
    editor.addEventListener('input', updatePreview);

    // Initialize
    editor.value = defaultContent;
    updatePreview();
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### How it works:
1.  **Layout:** Uses `flexbox` to create a perfect 50/50 split-screen view that adapts to mobile devices (stacks vertically on small screens).
2.  **Parsing Engine (`Marked.js`):** This is the heavy lifter. It converts the raw text from the `<textarea>` into valid HTML strings in real-time as you type.
3.  **Code Highlighting (`Highlight.js`):** I've integrated this via the `marked.setOptions` configuration. When it detects a code block (e.g., ` ```javascript `), it automatically applies color coding to that specific language.
4.  **Styling:** 
    *   The **Editor** uses a monospace font stack for a professional IDE feel.
    *   The **Previewer** is styled with "GitHub Dark" inspired CSS, ensuring that headers, blockquotes, and tables look exactly like they would on a major developer platform.
5.  **Performance:** It uses the `input` event listener, which is highly optimized for real-time updates without causing lag.
